issues.description: In the solution implementation (Lecture.java, lines 63–66), the toString method is declared to return Object rather than String. Because Object.toString() does not match the expected signature public String toString(), the @Override annotation will fail and the method will not correctly override Object.toString(), causing a compilation error and breaking the intended custom string behavior.
issues.suggested_fix: Change the toString method signature to return String (public String toString()) so it correctly overrides Object.toString().
